What is a Container?
Simple definition: A Container is like a box that can hold a child widget and style it with:

-Background color
-Padding (space inside)
-Margin (space outside)
-Borders
-Shadows
-Width and height
-Alignment

Think of it like: A <div> in HTML with CSS styling!

Container Properties Cheat Sheet============================================================================================

Property                 	What It Does	                    Example
child                   	Widget inside	                    child: Text('Hi')
color	                    Background color	                color: Colors.blue
width                   	Width in pixels	                  width: 200
height	                  Height in pixels	                height: 100
padding	                  Space inside	                    padding: EdgeInsets.all(20)
margin	                  Space outside	                    margin: EdgeInsets.all(10)
alignment	                Position child inside           	alignment: Alignment.center
decoration	              Borders, shadows, gradients	      decoration: BoxDecoration(...)
transform               	Rotate, scale, skew	              transform: Matrix4.rotationZ(0.1)
